Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive understanding. Let me create a detailed report of my findings.

## Comprehensive Exploration Report

### 1. Storybook Configuration

**Location:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/rnm-app-fintech-rewardprogram/.storybook/`

**Main Configuration** (`.storybook/main.ts`):
- Framework: `@storybook/react-native-web-vite`
- Stories pattern: `../src/**/*.stories.@(ts|tsx)` (looks for story files anywhere in src/)
- Transpiled modules include the design system: `@semparar/design-system-app`
- Path aliases configured:
  - `~` → `../src`
  - `~/store` → `.storybook/mocks/store.ts` (mocked for Storybook isolation)
  - `react-native-linear-gradient` → mocked version

**Preview Configuration** (`.storybook/preview.tsx`):
- Wraps all stories with `ThemeProvider` from `@semparar/design-system-app`
- Provides standard Storybook controls for color and date matching

**Mocks:**
- **Store Mock** (`.storybook/mocks/store.ts`): Creates a Zustand store with `setRewardsProgramSlices` for isolated testing
- **Linear Gradient Mock** (`.storybook/mocks/react-native-linear-gradient.tsx`): Simple View wrapper for web compatibility

**NPM Scripts:**
- `npm run storybook` → Runs dev server on port 6006
- `npm run build-storybook` → Production build

### 2. Existing Story Files

**Current Story:** `/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/rnm-app-fintech-rewardprogram/src/__stories__/SmokeTest.stories.tsx`

```typescript
import React from 'react';
import { View } from 'react-native';
import { Text, Button, Box } from '@semparar/design-system-app';
import type { Meta, StoryObj } from 'storybook/internal/types';

function SmokeTest() {
  return (
    <View style={{ padding: 24, gap: 16 }}>
      <Text type="headingMDL">Storybook Smoke Test</Text>
      <Text type="bodyMD">
        If you can read this, DS components render in Storybook.
      </Text>
      <Box pd="squishSmall" bgColor="LIGHT_BASE_02" br="sm">
        <Text type="bodySM">This is a Box with padding and background</Text>
      </Box>
      <Button text="DS Button" onPress={() => {}} />
    </View>
  );
}

const meta: Meta<typeof SmokeTest> = {
  title: 'SmokeTest/DS Components',
  component: SmokeTest,
};

export default meta;

type Story = StoryObj<typeof meta>;

export const Default: Story = {};
